result.name: Vegetarian Restaurant

reviews.text:
I’ve been coming here for years. They recently in the last three years had some deep clean. My dad comes back here when he’s in HK because the Chinese Vegetarian Food is always consistent. Over the years the meals that come with 4 small dishes and choice of noodle or rice has gotten more expensive but I love the Chinese Soup. My whole family is vegetarian and this place is almost as good as my moms cooking. 

I also like it because it’s a family that runs it and the parents are Taoist and have been around for a long time. It’s a nice stop if you are looking for something more fast and wet market shopping.

Hkd 45 per set 4 types of vege 1 soup. Worth the price and taste is good. Cheap n nice vegetarian shop is hard to find in Hong Kong. This is cheap & nice. Today is my 2nd visit of this shop , next time will try their fried mee hoon and loh pak gou. 🤤🤤
43$ for a set lunch with 4 curry, rice and soup is definitely worth it
Always good place for full vegetarian meal.  Only $42 for set lunch including soup and 4 choices.
我經常來的素食店，初一，十五派請有需要人士食飯我，善衆可捐餐。
